description: In 2015, the scandal exposed car manufacturers for cheating on diesel engine emissions tests. Now, advocacy groups are suing over the lack of recalls for the vast majority of affected vehicles and the excessive pollution that followed.

headline: A cappuccino war breaks out in Berlin
description: In the German capital, a coffee chain is booming on the promise of affordable prices. The success is generating as much enthusiasm as hostility, with some seeing it as the work of destructive 'turbo-capitalism.'

headline: The singular Georges de La Tour at the Musée Jacquemart-André
description: Some 30 works attributed to the French painter, whose life remains little known, are on display in Paris. In the absence of a clear chronology, the paintings have been categorized by subject − both secular and sacred.

headline: Antarctica's tourism boom accelerates melting of 'white continent'
description: While the number of tourists has skyrocketed over the past decade, the pristine continent, which is attracting growing interest among researchers, is gradually deteriorating.

description: From 'The Sting' to 'Out of Africa,' the actor and director embodied a certain kind of American cinema, generous and progressive. To encourage independent production, he created the Sundance Institute in 1981. He died on Tuesday, at the age of 89.

headline: Charlie Kirk assassination: The suspect's disconcerting profile
description: Tyler Robinson, arrested on Thursday night, is a 22-year-old White man who grew up in a conservative family in Utah and was a brilliant high school student. Nothing in his background supports the theory being propagated in MAGA circles that he is a far-left activist.

headline: The Paris district where Parisians are priced out
description: In 50 years, the 8th arrondissement of the French capital, home to the Champs-Elysées and the 'Golden Triangle,' has lost nearly half its population. The mass acquisition of real estate by ultra-wealthy foreigners has driven locals out.
